org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin

Interface WorkspacePlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExecContextPlugin

    public interface WorkspacePlugin
extends ExecContextPlugin
    TODO: The workspace implementation can and should know about the various types of directories (the various WorkspaceDir and SystemWorkspaceDir classes) and act accordingly. If it does not know about a specific class, maybe a default generic implementation is feasible. Maybe the workspace dir class could help in implementing such a defaul behavior (random vs fixed directory for instance).
    Author:
    David Raymond

      • isSupportMultipleModuleVersion

        boolean isSupportMultipleModuleVersion()
        Returns:
        Indicates if multiple Version's of the same Module can exist in user workspace directories.

      • isWorkspaceDirExist

        boolean isWorkspaceDirExist(WorkspaceDir workspaceDir)
        Verifies if a WorkspaceDir exists.

        The path to the WorkspaceDir may or may not exist. Only the knowledge of the WorkspaceDir within the workspace is verified.

        Parameters:
        workspaceDir - WorkspaceDir.
        Returns:
        See description.

      • getWorkspaceDirConflict

        WorkspaceDir getWorkspaceDirConflict(WorkspaceDir workspaceDir)
        Returns a conflicting WorkspaceDir with a given WorkspaceDir or null if none.

        A conflicting WorkspaceDir is one which maps to the same path.

        If isSupportMultipleModuleVersion() and the specified WorkspaceDir is for the same Module but a different Version, null should be returned.

        If it is for a different Module which would map to the same path as an existing WorkspaceDir, that WorkspaceDir should be returned.

        Parameters:
        workspaceDir - WorkspaceDir.
        Returns:
        See description.

      • getWorkspaceDir

        Path getWorkspaceDir(WorkspaceDir workspaceDir,
                     EnumSet<WorkspacePlugin.GetWorkspaceDirMode> enumSetGetWorkspaceDirMode,
                     WorkspacePlugin.WorkspaceDirAccessMode workspaceDirAccessMode)
        Returns the Path corresponding to the WorkspaceDir.

        Null cannot be returned. An exception is raised if thw WorkspaceDir does not exist or cannot be created.

        The WorkspaceDir must be released with releaseWorkspaceDir(java.nio.file.Path) unless WorkspacePlugin.WorkspaceDirAccessMode.PEEK was specified.

        Parameters:
        workspaceDir - WorkspaceDir.
        enumSetGetWorkspaceDirMode - EnumSet of GetWorkspaceDirMode.
        workspaceDirAccessMode - WorkspaceDirAccessMode.
        Returns:
        See description.

      • releaseWorkspaceDir

        void releaseWorkspaceDir(Path pathWorkspaceDir)
        Releases a WorkspaceDir given it corresponding Path.

        The WorkspaceDir must have been obtained with getWorkspaceDir(org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin.WorkspaceDir, java.util.EnumSet<org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin.WorkspacePlugin.GetWorkspaceDirMode>, org.azyva.dragom.execcontext.plugin.WorkspacePlugin.WorkspaceDirAccessMode).

        Parameters:
        pathWorkspaceDir - Path to the WorkspaceDir.

      • updateWorkspaceDir

        void updateWorkspaceDir(WorkspaceDir workspaceDir,
                        WorkspaceDir workspaceDirNew)
        Updates a WorkspaceDir.

        To be used when the ModuleVersion within the path corresponding to a WorkspaceDir is changed.

        The WorkspaceDir must be accessed for WorkspacePlugin.WorkspaceDirAccessMode.READ_WRITE.

        Parameters:
        workspaceDir - Current WorkspaceDir.
        workspaceDirNew - New WorkspaceDir.

      • deleteWorkspaceDir

        void deleteWorkspaceDir(WorkspaceDir workspaceDir)
        Deletes a WorkspaceDir and its corresponding path, if it exists.

        The WorkspaceDir must be accessed for WorkspacePlugin.WorkspaceDirAccessMode.READ_WRITE.

        Parameters:
        workspaceDir - WorkspaceDir.

      • getSetWorkspaceDir

        Set<WorkspaceDir> getSetWorkspaceDir(WorkspaceDir workspaceDirIncomplete)
        Returns the Set of all WorkspaceDir's matching some potentially incomplete WorkspaceDir definition.

        An example of an incomplete WorkspaceDir definition is a WorkspaceDirUserModuleVersion with a null Version.

        Parameters:
        workspaceDirIncomplete - Incomplete WorkspaceDir.

        See description.
